<div class="tldr-box">
  <h3>TL;DR, Perplexity for Indians</h3>
  <p>The right AI for "I need an answer with sources I can verify". Free tier is enough for casual users; Pro at ~₹1,690/month is worth it if you do research, journalism, or competitive analysis daily. Indian payment via card works directly; UPI is not supported.</p>
  <a href="https://www.perplexity.ai" class="cta-button">Try Perplexity (free)</a>
</div>

<p>Perplexity sits in a different bucket from ChatGPT or Claude. Those are conversational models that sometimes search the web; Perplexity is web search that answers in conversation. Every answer carries inline citations to actual sources, and you can click through to verify each claim.</p>

<p>For Indian users, this matters more than people first realize, ChatGPT and Claude often produce confidently wrong information about Indian tax, legal, and regulatory specifics. Perplexity is far less likely to hallucinate because it's anchored to current web sources at every step.</p>

<h2>What Perplexity costs Indian users</h2>

<table>
  <thead>
    <tr><th>Plan</th><th>Sticker</th><th>Approx INR</th><th>+ 18% GST</th><th>You pay (₹)</th></tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td>Free</td><td>$0</td><td>₹0</td><td>—</td><td>₹0</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Pro</td><td>$20/mo</td><td>~₹1,690</td><td>~₹304</td><td><strong>~₹1,994</strong></td></tr>
    <tr><td>Enterprise Pro</td><td>$40/user/mo</td><td>~₹3,380</td><td>~₹608</td><td><strong>~₹3,988/user</strong></td></tr>
    <tr><td>Pro annual</td><td>$200/yr</td><td>~₹16,900</td><td>~₹3,042</td><td><strong>~₹19,942/yr</strong></td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<p><em>Annual Pro is effectively ~₹1,662/month, a small saving. Most users start monthly.</em></p>

<h2>Free vs Pro</h2>

<h3>Free tier gives you</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Unlimited basic searches</li>
  <li>Up to 5 Pro searches per day (deeper, multi-step reasoning)</li>
  <li>Inline citations on every answer</li>
  <li>Web search with current information</li>
  <li>File upload (limited)</li>
</ul>

<h3>Pro adds</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Up to 600 Pro searches per day</li>
  <li>Choice of model (GPT-4o, Claude 4, Sonar Large, etc.)</li>
  <li>Image generation</li>
  <li>Pro file upload (PDFs, spreadsheets, larger limits)</li>
  <li>Spaces (collections of related research, sharable with team)</li>
  <li>API credits ($5/month included)</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Should you upgrade?</strong> If you find yourself hitting the 5-Pro-search-per-day cap, yes. Most casual users (15 minutes a day) live happily on free.</p>

<h2>How to pay for Perplexity from India</h2>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Indian credit cards</strong>, Most premium cards work; some require enabling international transactions</li>
  <li><strong>Forex cards (Niyo, HDFC Forex Plus)</strong>, Reliably work</li>
  <li><strong>Indian debit cards</strong>, Hit-and-miss, similar to ChatGPT</li>
  <li><strong>UPI</strong>, Not supported</li>
</ul>

<p>Payment friction is comparable to ChatGPT. If your card is rejected, the fix is to enable international transactions in your bank app or use a forex card.</p>

<h2>GST handling</h2>

<ul>
  <li>Perplexity charges 18% GST on Indian subscriptions</li>
  <li>Add your GSTIN at checkout for B2B invoice</li>
  <li>Tax invoice is emailed; you can claim input credit if registered</li>
  <li>Pro is a deductible business expense for income tax</li>
</ul>

<h2>Best Indian use cases</h2>

<h3>Journalists and researchers</h3>
<p>This is where Perplexity earns its keep. "What did the Supreme Court say about [topic] in the last six months?" returns a sourced answer with links to the actual orders, not a hallucinated summary. The Spaces feature lets you keep a running research file on a long-running story.</p>

<h3>UPSC and competitive exam aspirants</h3>
<p>Useful for current affairs preparation, every answer comes with citations to PIB, Hindu Editorials, and government sources. The "Discover" feed is decent for daily current affairs scanning.</p>

<h3>CAs, lawyers, consultants</h3>
<p>Indian tax and legal questions are where Perplexity beats ChatGPT and Claude by a clear margin. The citations let you check the actual section of the Act, the actual notification, the actual case law.</p>

<h3>Founders and analysts</h3>
<p>Competitive research, market sizing, regulatory landscape. Spaces let you keep separate research workspaces for different topics.</p>

<h3>Students writing thesis or term papers</h3>
<p>Sourced answers translate directly into citations for your bibliography. Faster than scrolling through 20 search results.</p>

<h2>What Perplexity is bad at</h2>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Long-form creative writing</strong>, Not the tool, use Claude or ChatGPT</li>
  <li><strong>Coding tasks</strong>, Possible but slow; use Claude or Copilot</li>
  <li><strong>Voice mode</strong>, Decent but not as polished as ChatGPT advanced voice</li>
  <li><strong>Casual conversation</strong>, Tone is research-paper-like, not a "chat companion"</li>
  <li><strong>Personal data analysis without context</strong>, Without web search, the model is weaker than dedicated chat models</li>
</ul>

<h2>Indian alternatives</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>ChatGPT Plus with web search</strong>, Search is now decent but citations are less reliable</li>
  <li><strong>Gemini with Deep Research</strong>, Strong free tier alternative for research</li>
  <li><strong>Google Scholar + ChatGPT</strong>, Manual but free</li>
  <li><strong>Sarvam AI</strong>, Indian model, weaker on real-time web</li>
</ul>

<h2>Indian-specific FAQs</h2>

<div class="faq-item">
  <h3>Is Perplexity free in India?</h3>
  <p>Yes. The free tier works without any India-specific restrictions. Indian phone numbers and email addresses are accepted.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
  <h3>Does Perplexity accept UPI?</h3>
  <p>Not directly. You will need an Indian credit card with international transactions enabled, or a forex card.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
  <h3>Why does Perplexity work better than ChatGPT for Indian topics?</h3>
  <p>Because it pulls from current Indian web sources at every step. ChatGPT relies on its training data, which often misses or misstates recent Indian regulatory changes, court orders, and news. Perplexity reads the actual source for each query.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
  <h3>Can I use Perplexity in Hindi?</h3>
  <p>Yes. Hindi queries work and Hindi sources (news, government sites) are surfaced when relevant. Output quality is good for Hindi but inconsistent for other Indian regional languages.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
  <h3>Is the free tier enough for an Indian college student?</h3>
  <p>For most use, yes. The 5-Pro-searches-per-day limit hits during deep assignment research. If you're writing a thesis, the ₹1,994/month for a couple of months is worth it.</p>
</div>

<h2>Final verdict</h2>

<p>For Indian users whose primary AI need is "answer this question accurately with sources I can verify", Perplexity is the cleanest tool on the market. The free tier is genuinely strong; Pro pays for itself if you do research, journalism, legal, or analyst work daily.</p>

<p>For pure conversation, creative writing, or coding, this is not the tool, pair Perplexity with Claude or ChatGPT.</p>

